list.abstract: some，英文单词，限定词、形容词、代词、副词、名词，作限定词时意为“一些；某些；好些；少量；某个；算不上；大约；至少有一点”，作形容词时意为“某个的；某些的；显著的；大量的；至少有一个的”，作代词时意为“（数量不确切时用）有些人，有些事物；部分”，作副词时意为“大约；稍微；（非正式）在某种程度上”，作名词时意为“（美、印）索梅（人名）”。
《some》是由SISTAR的昭宥和HIP-HOP歌手郑基高于2014年2月7日发行的歌曲，由金度勋作曲，闵延在作词，收录于昭宥和郑基高2014年2月7日的专辑《썸(Some)》中。 该曲音源公开后立即登上韩国国内各大主要音源排行榜一位，并获得韩国人民热烈凡响，后在“Gaon Chart K-POP Awards”上获得了五座奖杯。

direction_info.description:

<highlight> 考频分布</highlight>

word_family.mean: det. 若干；一些；某个；大约；大量的；可观的；至少有一点；了不起的；很不错的；一点也不

sense_info_list.en: an amount or number of something that is not stated or not known; a part of something

examination_example.sentence: But Mauna Kea is also home to <highlight>some</highlight> of the world's most powerful telescopes.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是莫纳基亚也是一些世界上最强大望远镜的所在地。

examination_example.sentence: Divorced persons are viewed with <highlight>some</highlight> disapproval.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 人们对离婚的人有些不以为然。

examination_example.sentence: As much as <highlight>some</highlight> scientists may complain about the new awards, two things seem clear.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 尽管一些科学家可能会抱怨新的奖项，但有两件事似乎很清楚。

examination_example.sentence: It's almost impossible to go through life without experiencing <highlight>some</highlight> kind of failure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 不经历某种失败就度过一生几乎是不可能的。

examination_example.sentence: How we read a given text also depends to <highlight>some</highlight> extent on our particular interest in reading it.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 我们如何阅读给定的文本在某种程度上也取决于我们对阅读文本的特殊兴趣。

examination_example.sentence: First, scientific work tends to focus on <highlight>some</highlight> aspect of prevailing knowledge that is viewed as incomplete or incorrect.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 首先，科学工作倾向于关注被视为不完整或不正确的流行知识的某些方面。

examination_example.sentence: The average supermarket, according to the Food Marketing Institute, carries <highlight>some</highlight> 44,000 different items.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据食品营销研究所的数据，普通的超市里大约有44000种不同的商品。

examination_example.sentence: But just <highlight>some</highlight> 22, 000 birds remain today, occupying about 16% of the species' historic range.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是今天只剩下大约22000只鸟，占该物种历史范围的16%。

examination_example.sentence: Companies had won patents for isolated DNA for decades — by 2005 <highlight>some</highlight> 20% of human genes were patented.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 几十年来，公司已经获得了分离DNA的专利——到2005年，大约20%的人类基因获得了专利。

examination_example.sentence: The zones do deliver <highlight>some</highlight> improvements to air quality.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这些区域确实大大改善了空气质量。

word_usage.usage:
some可以表示“某个”，与单数名词连用，表示未知或未确指的人、地、事物或时间。如：
If you are worried about some aspect of your child's health, call us.
如果你担心孩子某方面的健康问题，请给我们打电话。

examination_example.sentence: He was laughed at by <highlight>some</highlight> girls.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他被一些女孩嘲笑。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Some</highlight> claim that you want to force everyone to eat a vegetarian diet and make private transport illegal.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 一些人声称，你想强迫所有人吃素，并将私人交通定为非法。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Some</highlight> parents in China are overprotective of their children.

word_usage.usage: some在句中只用作定语，无比较等级。

some作“一些，一点”时，用于肯定句。若用于疑问句，表示期待肯定回答、请求或建议。
示例：Some people came to see her.
一些人来看她。
Would you have some tea?
喝点茶好吗?

some作“某个，某一”时，用于修饰单数名词；
He is working at some place in the north.
他在北方某地工作。

作“相当多的”时，可修饰不可数名词。
That was some speech you made!
你的演讲相当不错!

examination_example.sentence: Take <highlight>some</highlight> time to check out the buildings where your classes will be held.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 花点时间去看看你在哪里上课。

examination_example.sentence: He directed <highlight>some</highlight> high quality movies.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他导演了一些高质量的电影。

examination_example.sentence: They put <highlight>some</highlight> rice into a pot of water and left it to boil while they made the French toast.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们把一些米饭放进一壶水中，煮沸它的同时，他们做了法式吐司。

examination_example.sentence: Here you can enjoy 4 pours of <highlight>some</highlight> of the best wine San Francisco has to offer.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在这里你可以品尝到4杯旧金山最好的一些葡萄酒。

examination_example.sentence: <highlight>Some</highlight> of you may have heard of him before.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你们中的一些人以前可能听说过他。

examination_example.sentence: When I was twelve, I made a list of things I wanted to do <highlight>some</highlight> day.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 当我十二岁的时候，我把有朝一日想做的事情列了一个清单。

word_usage.usage:
some多用于肯定句中，在疑问句中多用any，但下述情况用some：
（1）用于请求中：
Will you have some bread?
你要来点面包吗？
（2）用于反问（难道…？）：
Aren't there some stamps in that drawer?
抽屉里难道没有邮票吗？

在条件句中，some/any都可用：
If we had some/any money,we could buy it.
如果我们有钱的话，我们就能买它。

disambiguation_list.sense_disambiguation:
some通常用在肯定句中，some还可以用在表示邀请、请求或期望得到肯定回答的疑问句中。
例：Would you like some tea?
你想要一些茶吗？

any通常用在否定句或疑问句中，any也可以用在肯定句中，和单数可数名词搭配，此时any 表示“任何”。
例：Take any book you like.
你喜欢哪本书就拿哪本。
